abstract_ssm: The Harold E. Weeks diaries are comprised of seven red cloth-bound diaries from the period 1925 to 1932 belonging to Harold Eastman Weeks (1886-1960).  The diaries include numerous newspaper clippings and enclosures, and contain day-to-day entries relating primarily to Weeks's professional activities as the Coordinating Engineer at the Brooklyn Edison Company.  The diaries also contain references to Weeks's personal, family and social lives.
